===Etymology===
*[[黙]] ''(moku, boku)'' = "silence."
*[[殺]] ''(satsu, setsu, sai, koro)'' = "to kill," "to murder."

===Verb phrase===
'''mokusatsu surú''', [[黙殺]][[する]]

#to [[take no notice of]]
#to shut one’s eyes
#to [[ignore]]
#to [[withhold]] [[comment]]
#to [[cut]] someone [[dead]]

'''Historical note:''' At the close of [[World War II]], then-Japanese Premier Kantaro Suzuki used this unfortunate choice of words in his reply to the [[U.S.]] demand for Japan’s [[unconditional]] [[surrender]] (the [[Potsdam Declaration]]).